name: Wild Turkey Kentucky Spirit Single Barrel
description: Each barrel hand selected under the watchful eye of legendary Master Distiller Jimmy Russell. Known for being fuller bodied, with rich vanilla flavors and a hint of sweetness, it’s the perfect bourbon to enjoy neat.
tastingNotes: A complex layering of almonds, honey, blackberries, and leather gives way to a long, dark and lingering finish.

name: Wild Turkey Longbranch
description: Culmination of a 24-month collaboration between Matthew McConaughey and Master Distiller Eddie Russell. This offering is initially oak-filtered, and then refined through Texas Mesquite charcoal.
tastingNotes:
Nose: butter toffee, vanilla, apple, caramel, honey-oak, nutmeg, orange peel, faint herbal spice.
Taste: vanilla, salted caramel, toasted oak, light baking spice, hints of leather & pepper.
Finish: medium-short, toasted caramel, vanilla, toffee, charred oak, roasted almonds, diminishing citrus zest & light herbal spice.

name: Russell's Reserve 10 Year
description: Part of Wild Turkey’s Russell’s Reserve line named in honor of Jimmy and Eddie Russell, the father-son master distiller team that have a combined tenure at Wild Turkey in excess of 100 years.
tastingNotes:
Nose: aromas of vanilla and caramel come forward, with whiffs of aged oak, graham cracker, and leather following.
Taste: caramel and vanilla notes resting against tobacco. and seasoned oak.
Finish: vestiges of toasted marshmallows, leather, tobacco, and again, fairly prominent caramel and vanilla notes.

name: Wild Turkey Rare Breed
description: Uncut with water, Rare Breed is an uncompromised Kentucky bourbon with tones of sweet tobacco and hints of orange and mint, making it a remarkably smooth whiskey legend.
tastingNotes:
Nose: Bold and spicy. Subtle hints of raw grains mingle with peppery seasoned wood.
Taste: Bold rye, pepper, and a small amount of seasoned oak give way to a developing sweetness.
Finish: Spicy rye and seasoned oak carry over into the finish, however sweet cane sugar, light caramelized wood, and vanilla take over.

name: Russell's Reserve Rye  6 Year
description: Uniquely smooth, hand selected small batch rye has a crisp, lively taste that they believe to be the perfect six-year-old rye.
tastingNotes:
Nose: aromas of vanilla and caramel come forward, with whiffs of aged oak, graham cracker, and leather following.
Taste: caramel and vanilla notes resting against tobacco. and seasoned oak.
Finish: vestiges of toasted marshmallows, leather, tobacco, and again, fairly prominent caramel and vanilla notes.

name: Wild Turkey Master's Keep Revival
description: Wild Turkey Master’s Keep Revival is the third release in the Master’s Keep series, after the 17 year old original and Decades, which paid tribute to Eddie Russell’s 35th Anniversary at Wild Turkey.
tastingNotes:
Nose: aromas of cherry pie, raisins, citrus, nuts and a touch of oak.
Taste: soft and creamy hints of spice and sweet tropical fruits.
Finish: long and lingering finish of dried apricots, honey and subtle spice.
mashbill: 75% Corn, 13% Rye, 12% Malted Barley. Finished in at least 20-year-old Oloroso Sherry casks, hand-selected by Master Distiller Eddie Russell.
